The Inspector-General Of Police, Usman Baba, has ordered the arrest and probe of music star, Habeeb Okikiola, popularly known as Portable, over his alleged ties to One Million Boys, a notorious cultist gang.
IGP disclosed this in a statement issued by Force Public Relations Officer, Muyiwa Adejobi, on Monday.
In a video, which went viral on Monday, Portable was heard saying he formed the cultist group and another notorious group known as Ajah Boys.
“Open your ears and hear me, Have you heard about Ajah Boys, One Million Boys, I’m their founder. Go and ask Sammy larry,” he said.
The singer spoke Yoruba in the now-deleted video.
 
